description:
Welcome Ladies to Girls In Stockholm!

Girls In Stockholm invites all ladies from all walks of life to join our friendly and lively atmosphere. We are a collection of women from all parts of the world of all ages who come together to share experiences and build lifelong bonds. Once a month, we gather for our monthly fika get together, but throughout the year we also offer a variety of activities which appeal to all types of women.

Event categories:

Outdoor Activities

• Excursions 

• Fitness

• Fun Brunches

 Indoor Activities

• Crafts

• Baking

• Bookclub/Kindle

• Social Fika Intro to Stockholm


Any other suggestions will be welcome. So please do not hesitate to get in touch.


New Girls In Stockholm RSVP rules.

As our organisers and hosts give up their time to arrange these events there will now be a minimum deposit of 50kr when RSVPing. 

When an event is free this money will be refunded upon attendance or a cancellation. Provided the cancellation is in the allotted time.

If these rules are not followed you will immediately be removed from the Girls In Stockholm.
I hope by doing this it will decrease disappointment and let down and encourage friendships and fun.

So with that happy belated New Year from Toyah, Becki Harriet and Shona

category.name: socializing
description:
This is a group for people who enjoy the Swedish (and Scandinavian) tradition of fika. We usually meet Saturday or Sunday morning for open-minded discussions of things from making good food to how to find your way in Swedish society. Foreigners living here, Swedes and visitors all welcome to join!

For those who have recently arrived or might have missed it, fika ("fee-ka") is a social institution in Sweden, and in its basic form means having a break with something light to eat and drink. Traditionally it resembles a coffee break, but the beverage can equally well be tea, juice, lemonade or even milk. This is usually accompanied by something sweet, for example a cinnamon roll or cookies. It's an important part of Swedish culture, and a great way to get together and talk about things great and small.

description:
Come join those who like exploring Stockholm on foot, supplied only with sunglasses + smartphone + bottle of water set. 

We define some preliminary route in advance, then on a sunny day step on the road and go! Every meetup is about 2+ hours of walking together in the picturesque surroundings, taking pics, reading out the areas description from wiki or whatever can educate us about the city history and architecture, resting shortly in nearby cafes or places of interest, etc. 

It's all like being a tourist, but why not! Everyday routine somewhat obscures the beauty and the spirit of the city, so let's rediscover it!

P.S. You can also organize walk events yourself! We are democracy and each member can schedule a meetup and invite people for walk!

category.name: socializing
description:
This Meetup is about having fun and interesting meetings in acknowledgement and recognition of the fact that how we live our days is how we live our lives.

This sounds rather stuffy and formal and boring, but it isn't meant that way. :-)

I am hoping this group will be intellectually curious and wanting to learn and expand its horizon. Let's do meaningful and fun indoor and outdoor activities and try to meet people we will enjoy being around.

Let's pursue such varied interests as hiking and climbing, literature and movies, the martial arts, science and technology, blockchain and economics, entrepreneurship, Paleo/Primal health, eating out, trigger points, parkour, philosophy, and similar stuff - 'stuff' understood here in the highly specific technical sense.

If this sounds like it could be interesting, please join!

By the way, curious about the name? Seneca wrote (hat tip to Brain Pickings https://www.brainpickings.org/2014/09/01/seneca-on-the-shortness-of-life/ for the find):

"It is not that we have a short time to live, but that we waste a lot of it. Life is long enough, and a sufficiently generous amount has been given to us for the highest achievements if it were all well invested. But when it is wasted in heedless luxury and spent on no good activity, we are forced at last by death’s final constraint to realize that it has passed away before we knew it was passing. So it is: we are not given a short life but we make it short, and we are not ill-supplied but wasteful of it… Life is long if you know how to use it."

Group guidelines

- Please cancel any RSVPs if you can't attend - that helps with any bookings, keeping expectations in line, etc.

- Tired of having people upload photos taken of yourself already during the first meet up? Same here - please ask if you'd like to take somebody's photo

- We adhere to the Chatham House Rule: https://www.chathamhouse.org/about/chatham-...

Have fun :-)
name: Living like Seneca

category.name: socializing
description:
Les Francophones de Copenhague est une association dynamique, non lucrative, dont l'objectif est de permettre aux différents francophones (citoyens de pays francophones, danois francophones et toutes les personnes desirant parler la langue française ) de se rencontrer. Le but de ce groupe est aussi de se faire des amis et de passer d'agréables moments ensemble.

Quelle que soit la raison pour laquelle vous êtes au Danemark (travail, /etudes ou amour), l'arrivée peut être depaysante et solitaire. L'inscription aux Francophones est gratuite et vous êtes libres de choisir les activités auxquelles vous désirez participer. Les organisateurs des Francophones sont bénévoles et organisent les meetups pour le plaisir de rencontrer de nouvelles personnes et de faciliter l'intégration sociale des nouveaux venus.

En devenant membres des Francophones, vous pourrez participer à nos rencontres. La majorité d'entre nous travaillant, les événements ont lieu en soirée ou/et les week-ends. Nos activités incluent rencontres dans des bars, visites de musée, cinéma, conférences (notamment avec l'Institut Français du Danemark) et bien plus. Donc n'hésitez pas à vous inscrire, il y en a pour tous les goûts.

WE ARE HAPPY TO WELCOME DANISH PEOPLE INTO THIS GROUP :-) DON'T BE SHY, JOIN US !!! À bientôt! Vi ses! :-)

category.name: socializing
description:
SOSO BRINGING INTERNATIONALS AND DANES TOGETHER

So Sophisticated started three years ago in a cozy bar with 50 invited friends and acquaintances. It was a mix of internationals and Danes who were encouraged to bring some of their friends along for a comfortable way to socialize while meeting new people and making new friends. Over 100 people ended up coming that very first night and thus, SOSO was born! 

The SOSO initiative was founded on people new to Copenhagen having an opportunity to mix and mingle with Danes for networking and expanding their social circle while getting out and about, being exposed to new places around town for great cocktails. 

For those that may not know a soul and are a bit shy, the people that attend SOSO are welcoming and friendly. You are sure to meet some very nice and interesting people. SOSO is made up of an eclectic bunch of people from ages 25 to 45 who are professionals and students all looking forward to meet you. For those that are outgoing or been with SOSO from the start, it's appreciated that you reach out to the new faces and introduce them to others you know. It's all about getting to know each other. Through SOSO past guests have found new jobs, great friends and even romance.

Come spread the love. We hope to see you and your friends at our next event.

Cheers!
Maria Fazzingo - Founder
Anders Hage - Event Organizer and Host
name: The Copenhagen SOSO Monthly Cocktail Social Club Meetup Grp

description: Welcome! The expat experience is a life less ordinary. An experience where the value of connections and richness of relations can make the difference between good and great. By connecting spouses who have travelled, lived and worked around the globe we hope to create a fun, inspiring and dynamic group, where we can help each other and share all kinds of experiences and practical advice related to life, travel, family and work in Denmark. As the daughter of an expatriate I grew up in Canada, Egypt and Ivory Coast, and I have spent the last 16 years in Copenhagen. I have worked in the hotel and hospitality business for many years, run my own fashion clothing business and worked in the UN for the last 6 years. Our group is open to all spouses of expatriates and their families as well as Danish expats returning after a few or many years abroad. We are looking forward to hosting a broad array of fun activities and offering you a cosy, warm space to relax and share. Our activities will take place during the day and in the evening, on week days as well as on weekends. Lets make our Copenhagen stay into a fabulous one. See you soon!
name: Copenhagen Expat Spouse meetup

description: Meeting new people can be fun... meeting couples can be twice as much!. This is a group intended for couples only, so we'll consider everyone who joins as an RSVP+1, which means you are in a relationship, have a wifey or a hubby, a partner, a boo or a bae, a special someone, a significant other, however you wanna call it, the thing is you're not alone and will always attend in pairs. Our events will be tailored for couples: dinner parties, BBQs, boat trips, picnics, sightseeing, bike rides, movies, game nights, etc., and all RSVPs will be counted as two people, even when not adding the plus one. Our motto is to build long term friendships, having fun together, learning from and supporting each other. Please know that you must be at least (or soon to be) 30 years old to join us.

category.name: socializing
description:
This group was formed with the aim of expats, and locals for that matter, having the opportunity to meet new people in a comfortable environment. This is a group based on meeting up casually in a bar, park, an outdoor area, or anywhere for that matter. It is about enjoying company, relaxing and having fun over a beer, wine, coffee or any type of drink, anywhere, anytime. 

We are a social group where everyone is welcome, we respect all others in the group (it is not a dating meetup group). 

There is only one expectation in this group: Have fun! If you do not enjoy a meetup, or the venue, then it is best not to come! This group is judgement free. 

Also, please do not hesitate to PM me if you would like to catch up for a coffee or drink at anytime. I hope to see you soon.
name: Copenhagen Casual Meetup Group

category.name: socializing
description:
Our meetup group is organised through the Southern Cross Club. A club for Aussies, Kiwis and their families living in Denmark. Or anyone else with an interest in socialising with Aussies and Kiwis in Denmark.

The club is undoubtedly the oldest club in Denmark. Well before the days of the internet the club was organising a few events each year, and members came from all over Denmark. Today the club is re-establishing itself using social media with the same original intention.

We're looking at different types of events, such as dinners out, pub quizzes, walks in the forest, barbies (of course!), weekends camping, Anzac Day, Christmas parties, etc., etc. All are welcome to use the meetup site to organise or announce their own events.

Find us on Facebook

The Committee - Southern Cross Club, Denmark

description:
Are you a woman loving brunch and looking to make new friends in Copenhagen? If the answer is yes then this is the meetup for you! The objective is to get together on a Saturday/Sunday morning for some brunch/chats and meet new friends. Once a month we'll organize a brunch – from low key to very fancy.

Please be aware that this is a community-driven page that encourages active membership. If you haven't been active in the group for more than 5 month we'll remove you to make room for new members. However, you're always welcome to join us again at a later point. Looking forward to meet you at our next brunch!

This group is limited to 50 members, we therefore have also created a Facebook group where we'll annonce free spots: https://www.facebook.com/groups/587682711569889/

Looking forward to see you at the next brunch!
Martina & Leah

category.name: socializing
description:
Esoteric, for non-native English speakers, is something that is known only by a few people i.e. not mainstream.
As a person who has an avid interest in travel, I would love to go to some places that are quite absurd for many other people. Personally, I engage in travel in a more cultural and leisure way rather than an adventure. That's why I've created this meetup; to find other weirdos like me.
These are places where most of us do not know anybody (although it would be amazing if someone did), where it's hard to convince your friends to travel to, and which are not great for solo travel either.
Some places I have in mind are:
1. The Faroe Islands
2. Riga, Latvia
3. Skopje, Macedonia
4. Tallinn, Estonia
5. Dresden, Germany
Obviously, everyone else can add their own list and we can decide on a place that suits the most number of people. A reasonable target would be to have at least 3 trips in 2018. I would prefer weekend trips, hence the choice of places that are not too far away from CPH and reasonably cheap to fly to. However, this doesn't have to be the case for others. I just want to bring together people with a similar taste, and decide together. About me: 25-year-old Indian guy who moved to CPH last year from the US. I've saved up and ready to take advantage of my Schengen visa with a rather ambitious goal of visiting 12 countries this year.
name: Esoteric European Travel (20's and 30's)

description:
Les Francophones de Copenhague est une association dynamique, non lucrative, dont l'objectif est de permettre aux différents francophones (citoyens de pays francophones, danois francophones et toutes les personnes desirant parler la langue française ) de se rencontrer. Le but de ce groupe est aussi de se faire des amis et de passer d'agréables moments ensemble.

Quelle que soit la raison pour laquelle vous êtes au Danemark (travail, /etudes ou amour), l'arrivée peut être depaysante et solitaire. L'inscription aux Francophones est gratuite et vous êtes libres de choisir les activités auxquelles vous désirez participer. Les organisateurs des Francophones sont bénévoles et organisent les meetups pour le plaisir de rencontrer de nouvelles personnes et de faciliter l'intégration sociale des nouveaux venus.

En devenant membres des Francophones, vous pourrez participer à nos rencontres. La majorité d'entre nous travaillant, les événements ont lieu en soirée ou/et les week-ends. Nos activités incluent rencontres dans des bars, visites de musée, cinéma, conférences (notamment avec l'Institut Français du Danemark) et bien plus. Donc n'hésitez pas à vous inscrire, il y en a pour tous les goûts.

WE ARE HAPPY TO WELCOME DANISH PEOPLE INTO THIS GROUP :-) DON'T BE SHY, JOIN US !!! À bientôt! Vi ses! :-)
name: Les Francophones de Copenhague

category.name: socializing
description:
SOSO BRINGING INTERNATIONALS AND DANES TOGETHER

So Sophisticated started three years ago in a cozy bar with 50 invited friends and acquaintances. It was a mix of internationals and Danes who were encouraged to bring some of their friends along for a comfortable way to socialize while meeting new people and making new friends. Over 100 people ended up coming that very first night and thus, SOSO was born! 

The SOSO initiative was founded on people new to Copenhagen having an opportunity to mix and mingle with Danes for networking and expanding their social circle while getting out and about, being exposed to new places around town for great cocktails. 

For those that may not know a soul and are a bit shy, the people that attend SOSO are welcoming and friendly. You are sure to meet some very nice and interesting people. SOSO is made up of an eclectic bunch of people from ages 25 to 45 who are professionals and students all looking forward to meet you. For those that are outgoing or been with SOSO from the start, it's appreciated that you reach out to the new faces and introduce them to others you know. It's all about getting to know each other. Through SOSO past guests have found new jobs, great friends and even romance.

Come spread the love. We hope to see you and your friends at our next event.

Cheers!
Maria Fazzingo - Founder
Anders Hage - Event Organizer and Host
name: The Copenhagen SOSO Monthly Cocktail Social Club Meetup Grp

We will: work for integration between a broad number ud cultures and nationalities. Work for understanding and break down frontiers. We arrange a number of events where families can participate as well, the meetup is for everybody!

Please note we are a non-profit meetup and no publicity for private businesses is allowed, excpt for sponsorships of course.

description: Welcome! The expat experience is a life less ordinary. An experience where the value of connections and richness of relations can make the difference between good and great. By connecting spouses who have travelled, lived and worked around the globe we hope to create a fun, inspiring and dynamic group, where we can help each other and share all kinds of experiences and practical advice related to life, travel, family and work in Denmark. As the daughter of an expatriate I grew up in Canada, Egypt and Ivory Coast, and I have spent the last 16 years in Copenhagen. I have worked in the hotel and hospitality business for many years, run my own fashion clothing business and worked in the UN for the last 6 years. Our group is open to all spouses of expatriates and their families as well as Danish expats returning after a few or many years abroad. We are looking forward to hosting a broad array of fun activities and offering you a cosy, warm space to relax and share. Our activities will take place during the day and in the evening, on week days as well as on weekends. Lets make our Copenhagen stay into a fabulous one. See you soon!
name: Copenhagen Expat Spouse meetup

category.name: socializing
description: Meeting new people can be fun... meeting couples can be twice as much!. This is a group intended for couples only, so we'll consider everyone who joins as an RSVP+1, which means you are in a relationship, have a wifey or a hubby, a partner, a boo or a bae, a special someone, a significant other, however you wanna call it, the thing is you're not alone and will always attend in pairs. Our events will be tailored for couples: dinner parties, BBQs, boat trips, picnics, sightseeing, bike rides, movies, game nights, etc., and all RSVPs will be counted as two people, even when not adding the plus one. Our motto is to build long term friendships, having fun together, learning from and supporting each other. Please know that you must be at least (or soon to be) 30 years old to join us.
name: Plus 1: Copenhagen's couples only Meetup group

description:
Café Cadeau is a non profit café and more, it's a cafe designed with community-building as a base. 

The mission is not just to draw people in, but most importantly, that internationals & danes can build friendships & together, have the chance to contribute to Copenhagen through different projects. 

We express this through a volunteering platform where, members of our community freely give their time to either create fun activities or help others with practical needs such as -  advice in the areas of economy, legal rights and health among others. Together, we want to create value in the community. 

Café Cadeau - coffee, people and culture.

category.name: socializing
description:
This group was formed with the aim of expats, and locals for that matter, having the opportunity to meet new people in a comfortable environment. This is a group based on meeting up casually in a bar, park, an outdoor area, or anywhere for that matter. It is about enjoying company, relaxing and having fun over a beer, wine, coffee or any type of drink, anywhere, anytime. 

We are a social group where everyone is welcome, we respect all others in the group (it is not a dating meetup group). 

There is only one expectation in this group: Have fun! If you do not enjoy a meetup, or the venue, then it is best not to come! This group is judgement free. 

Also, please do not hesitate to PM me if you would like to catch up for a coffee or drink at anytime. I hope to see you soon.
name: Copenhagen Casual Meetup Group

Social Nights: Join us for pre-drinks/happy hour and continuing with the night at any of the nightclubs we set out for us to enjoy!

The Awesome Race: A custom designed event for users to explore the city.

description:
Our meetup group is organised through the Southern Cross Club. A club for Aussies, Kiwis and their families living in Denmark. Or anyone else with an interest in socialising with Aussies and Kiwis in Denmark.

The club is undoubtedly the oldest club in Denmark. Well before the days of the internet the club was organising a few events each year, and members came from all over Denmark. Today the club is re-establishing itself using social media with the same original intention.

We're looking at different types of events, such as dinners out, pub quizzes, walks in the forest, barbies (of course!), weekends camping, Anzac Day, Christmas parties, etc., etc. All are welcome to use the meetup site to organise or announce their own events.

Find us on Facebook

The Committee - Southern Cross Club, Denmark

description:
Are you a woman loving brunch and looking to make new friends in Copenhagen? If the answer is yes then this is the meetup for you! The objective is to get together on a Saturday/Sunday morning for some brunch/chats and meet new friends. Once a month we'll organize a brunch – from low key to very fancy.

Please be aware that this is a community-driven page that encourages active membership. If you haven't been active in the group for more than 5 month we'll remove you to make room for new members. However, you're always welcome to join us again at a later point. Looking forward to meet you at our next brunch!

This group is limited to 50 members, we therefore have also created a Facebook group where we'll annonce free spots: https://www.facebook.com/groups/587682711569889/

Looking forward to see you at the next brunch!
Martina & Leah
name: Ladies who brunch - Copenhagen

category.name: socializing
description:
Esoteric, for non-native English speakers, is something that is known only by a few people i.e. not mainstream.
As a person who has an avid interest in travel, I would love to go to some places that are quite absurd for many other people. Personally, I engage in travel in a more cultural and leisure way rather than an adventure. That's why I've created this meetup; to find other weirdos like me.
These are places where most of us do not know anybody (although it would be amazing if someone did), where it's hard to convince your friends to travel to, and which are not great for solo travel either.
Some places I have in mind are:
1. The Faroe Islands
2. Riga, Latvia
3. Skopje, Macedonia
4. Tallinn, Estonia
5. Dresden, Germany
Obviously, everyone else can add their own list and we can decide on a place that suits the most number of people. A reasonable target would be to have at least 3 trips in 2018. I would prefer weekend trips, hence the choice of places that are not too far away from CPH and reasonably cheap to fly to. However, this doesn't have to be the case for others. I just want to bring together people with a similar taste, and decide together. About me: 25-year-old Indian guy who moved to CPH last year from the US. I've saved up and ready to take advantage of my Schengen visa with a rather ambitious goal of visiting 12 countries this year.
name: Esoteric European Travel (20's and 30's)

description:
By joining the Helsingør - Helsingborg (HH-Meetup) group you will: - participate in common cultural  events and nature excursions in North-west Skaane and Nordsjaelland - get new friends, new opportunities on both sides of oeresund - contribute to H-H and Oeresund as one region - spend a good time in company with good friends - occasionally share events with Meetup groups in Malmö, CPH, Kristianstad and Lund. In some cases you have to count on transport with the boat.

We will: work for integration between a broad number ud cultures and nationalities. Work for understanding and break down frontiers. We arrange a number of events where families can participate as well, the meetup is for everybody!

Please note we are a non-profit meetup and no publicity for private businesses is allowed, excpt for sponsorships of course.

description:
Hello, My name's Sidi. I've been living and working in Sweden for 5 years (3 in Uppsala and 2 in Lund). Meetup is has been the best way to get to know new people, make new friends, do some activities (Pub, restaurant, party, sport, travel and many more). Now i am moving to Örebro for work and would like to to have similar thing. The idea is simple, if you have an idea for a fun activity (sport, bar, book club, language exchange...etc), u just need to make an event and see who's up for it. If few people sign up, i might set a few "regular events" depending on people's wishes.

So just keep calm and socialize. +++
Sidi.

We are a growing group, getting more and more members, so join or create an event and prepare to meet some new friends! :-)

I hope to get to know you!
/Anna, Organizer

description:
Are you thinking about creating a new meetup group in Umeå? Are you an existing organizer of a meetup group in Umeå? Have you been organizing events before, and are willing to share your knowledge? This group is for you.

How to advertise the events and the group? Where to do it? How to make events captivating, exciting, and fun? How to engage people? What to do? How to plan? How often to meet? When to have a meetup event that would not collide with another meetup group? etc.

This group is aimed to be a union of meetup organizers in Umeå, who wish to share advices and ideas to others organizers, or to people would like to create a new group in order to meet likeminded people around a topic.

We're not competitors. Let's help each other...

description:
We are a group of women who get together to socialize, celebrate and enjoy being American. Yes that includes celebrating the 4th of July, Thanksgiving, and more! AWCG is primarily a support group for fellow American expats, but it is also great way to meet new people, have access to a great network of women, and find a piece of home away from home. If you have a question, we've probably asked it. We are a wealth of information and always willing to share our experiences.

Not an American expat? We also welcome non-citizen ladies with strong connections to the U.S. such as having an American sambo or children, or those who have worked, lived, or studied in the U.S. for a long period of time.

Learn more about us on our website.

Unsure if this club is for you? Please send an inquiry to membership(at)awcgothenburg.com before filling out a membership form.

category.name: socializing
description:
Make new friends from different countries, cultures and hangout with some local as well in multiple venues around the city.

Most of us folks (be it expats, professionals business people, entrepreneurs or local Swedes from different city) living in Gothenburg, Sweden knows how difficult it could be sometimes finding and making new friends here and expanding our social networking. This group plan to change that and facilitate an environment where people can easily mingle and make news friend or catch up with old ones around various social events.

This group plan to organise at many events a month all around the city, some at public venue and other by invite only. There will possibly be more events planned in the future as the group grows.


It is basically a gathering spot for meeting local, multicultural and international mix of people, a great way to spend day or evening with bunch of similar people and social activities you like.

category.name: socializing
description:
Welcome Ladies to Girls In Stockholm!

Girls In Stockholm invites all ladies from all walks of life to join our friendly and lively atmosphere. We are a collection of women from all parts of the world of all ages who come together to share experiences and build lifelong bonds. Once a month, we gather for our monthly fika get together, but throughout the year we also offer a variety of activities which appeal to all types of women.

Event categories:

Outdoor Activities

• Excursions 

• Fitness

• Fun Brunches

 Indoor Activities

• Crafts

• Baking

• Bookclub/Kindle

• Social Fika Intro to Stockholm


Any other suggestions will be welcome. So please do not hesitate to get in touch.


New Girls In Stockholm RSVP rules.

As our organisers and hosts give up their time to arrange these events there will now be a minimum deposit of 50kr when RSVPing. 

When an event is free this money will be refunded upon attendance or a cancellation. Provided the cancellation is in the allotted time.

If these rules are not followed you will immediately be removed from the Girls In Stockholm.
I hope by doing this it will decrease disappointment and let down and encourage friendships and fun.

So with that happy belated New Year from Toyah, Becki Harriet and Shona

description:
This is a group for people who enjoy the Swedish (and Scandinavian) tradition of fika. We usually meet Saturday or Sunday morning for open-minded discussions of things from making good food to how to find your way in Swedish society. Foreigners living here, Swedes and visitors all welcome to join!

For those who have recently arrived or might have missed it, fika ("fee-ka") is a social institution in Sweden, and in its basic form means having a break with something light to eat and drink. Traditionally it resembles a coffee break, but the beverage can equally well be tea, juice, lemonade or even milk. This is usually accompanied by something sweet, for example a cinnamon roll or cookies. It's an important part of Swedish culture, and a great way to get together and talk about things great and small.

description:
Come join those who like exploring Stockholm on foot, supplied only with sunglasses + smartphone + bottle of water set. 

We define some preliminary route in advance, then on a sunny day step on the road and go! Every meetup is about 2+ hours of walking together in the picturesque surroundings, taking pics, reading out the areas description from wiki or whatever can educate us about the city history and architecture, resting shortly in nearby cafes or places of interest, etc. 

It's all like being a tourist, but why not! Everyday routine somewhat obscures the beauty and the spirit of the city, so let's rediscover it!

P.S. You can also organize walk events yourself! We are democracy and each member can schedule a meetup and invite people for walk!

category.name: socializing
description:
This Meetup is about having fun and interesting meetings in acknowledgement and recognition of the fact that how we live our days is how we live our lives.

This sounds rather stuffy and formal and boring, but it isn't meant that way. :-)

I am hoping this group will be intellectually curious and wanting to learn and expand its horizon. Let's do meaningful and fun indoor and outdoor activities and try to meet people we will enjoy being around.

Let's pursue such varied interests as hiking and climbing, literature and movies, the martial arts, science and technology, blockchain and economics, entrepreneurship, Paleo/Primal health, eating out, trigger points, parkour, philosophy, and similar stuff - 'stuff' understood here in the highly specific technical sense.

If this sounds like it could be interesting, please join!

By the way, curious about the name? Seneca wrote (hat tip to Brain Pickings https://www.brainpickings.org/2014/09/01/seneca-on-the-shortness-of-life/ for the find):

"It is not that we have a short time to live, but that we waste a lot of it. Life is long enough, and a sufficiently generous amount has been given to us for the highest achievements if it were all well invested. But when it is wasted in heedless luxury and spent on no good activity, we are forced at last by death’s final constraint to realize that it has passed away before we knew it was passing. So it is: we are not given a short life but we make it short, and we are not ill-supplied but wasteful of it… Life is long if you know how to use it."

Group guidelines

- Please cancel any RSVPs if you can't attend - that helps with any bookings, keeping expectations in line, etc.

- Tired of having people upload photos taken of yourself already during the first meet up? Same here - please ask if you'd like to take somebody's photo

- We adhere to the Chatham House Rule: https://www.chathamhouse.org/about/chatham-...

Have fun :-)
name: Living like Seneca

category.name: socializing
description:
We are a group of women who get together to socialize, celebrate and enjoy being American. Yes that includes celebrating the 4th of July, Thanksgiving, and more! AWCG is primarily a support group for fellow American expats, but it is also great way to meet new people, have access to a great network of women, and find a piece of home away from home. If you have a question, we've probably asked it. We are a wealth of information and always willing to share our experiences.

Not an American expat? We also welcome non-citizen ladies with strong connections to the U.S. such as having an American sambo or children, or those who have worked, lived, or studied in the U.S. for a long period of time.

Learn more about us on our website.

description:
Welcome Ladies to Girls In Stockholm!

Girls In Stockholm invites all ladies from all walks of life to join our friendly and lively atmosphere. We are a collection of women from all parts of the world of all ages who come together to share experiences and build lifelong bonds. Once a month, we gather for our monthly fika get together, but throughout the year we also offer a variety of activities which appeal to all types of women.

Event categories:

Outdoor Activities

• Excursions 

• Fitness

• Fun Brunches

 Indoor Activities

• Crafts

• Baking

• Bookclub/Kindle

• Social Fika Intro to Stockholm


Any other suggestions will be welcome. So please do not hesitate to get in touch.


New Girls In Stockholm RSVP rules.

As our organisers and hosts give up their time to arrange these events there will now be a minimum deposit of 50kr when RSVPing. 

When an event is free this money will be refunded upon attendance or a cancellation. Provided the cancellation is in the allotted time.

If these rules are not followed you will immediately be removed from the Girls In Stockholm.
I hope by doing this it will decrease disappointment and let down and encourage friendships and fun.

So with that happy belated New Year from Toyah, Becki Harriet and Shona

description:
This is a group for people who enjoy the Swedish (and Scandinavian) tradition of fika. We usually meet Saturday or Sunday morning for open-minded discussions of things from making good food to how to find your way in Swedish society. Foreigners living here, Swedes and visitors all welcome to join!

For those who have recently arrived or might have missed it, fika ("fee-ka") is a social institution in Sweden, and in its basic form means having a break with something light to eat and drink. Traditionally it resembles a coffee break, but the beverage can equally well be tea, juice, lemonade or even milk. This is usually accompanied by something sweet, for example a cinnamon roll or cookies. It's an important part of Swedish culture, and a great way to get together and talk about things great and small.

description:
Come join those who like exploring Stockholm on foot, supplied only with sunglasses + smartphone + bottle of water set. 

We define some preliminary route in advance, then on a sunny day step on the road and go! Every meetup is about 2+ hours of walking together in the picturesque surroundings, taking pics, reading out the areas description from wiki or whatever can educate us about the city history and architecture, resting shortly in nearby cafes or places of interest, etc. 

It's all like being a tourist, but why not! Everyday routine somewhat obscures the beauty and the spirit of the city, so let's rediscover it!

P.S. You can also organize walk events yourself! We are democracy and each member can schedule a meetup and invite people for walk!

category.name: socializing
description:
This Meetup is about having fun and interesting meetings in acknowledgement and recognition of the fact that how we live our days is how we live our lives.

This sounds rather stuffy and formal and boring, but it isn't meant that way. :-)

I am hoping this group will be intellectually curious and wanting to learn and expand its horizon. Let's do meaningful and fun indoor and outdoor activities and try to meet people we will enjoy being around.

Let's pursue such varied interests as hiking and climbing, literature and movies, the martial arts, science and technology, blockchain and economics, entrepreneurship, Paleo/Primal health, eating out, trigger points, parkour, philosophy, and similar stuff - 'stuff' understood here in the highly specific technical sense.

If this sounds like it could be interesting, please join!

By the way, curious about the name? Seneca wrote (hat tip to Brain Pickings https://www.brainpickings.org/2014/09/01/seneca-on-the-shortness-of-life/ for the find):

"It is not that we have a short time to live, but that we waste a lot of it. Life is long enough, and a sufficiently generous amount has been given to us for the highest achievements if it were all well invested. But when it is wasted in heedless luxury and spent on no good activity, we are forced at last by death’s final constraint to realize that it has passed away before we knew it was passing. So it is: we are not given a short life but we make it short, and we are not ill-supplied but wasteful of it… Life is long if you know how to use it."

Group guidelines

- Please cancel any RSVPs if you can't attend - that helps with any bookings, keeping expectations in line, etc.

- Tired of having people upload photos taken of yourself already during the first meet up? Same here - please ask if you'd like to take somebody's photo

- We adhere to the Chatham House Rule: https://www.chathamhouse.org/about/chatham-...

Have fun :-)
name: Living like Seneca

description:
Welcome Ladies to Girls In Stockholm!

Girls In Stockholm invites all ladies from all walks of life to join our friendly and lively atmosphere. We are a collection of women from all parts of the world of all ages who come together to share experiences and build lifelong bonds. Once a month, we gather for our monthly fika get together, but throughout the year we also offer a variety of activities which appeal to all types of women.

Event categories:

Outdoor Activities

• Excursions 

• Fitness

• Fun Brunches

 Indoor Activities

• Crafts

• Baking

• Bookclub/Kindle

• Social Fika Intro to Stockholm


Any other suggestions will be welcome. So please do not hesitate to get in touch.


New Girls In Stockholm RSVP rules.

As our organisers and hosts give up their time to arrange these events there will now be a minimum deposit of 50kr when RSVPing. 

When an event is free this money will be refunded upon attendance or a cancellation. Provided the cancellation is in the allotted time.

If these rules are not followed you will immediately be removed from the Girls In Stockholm.
I hope by doing this it will decrease disappointment and let down and encourage friendships and fun.

So with that happy belated New Year from Toyah, Becki Harriet and Shona

description:
This is a group for people who enjoy the Swedish (and Scandinavian) tradition of fika. We usually meet Saturday or Sunday morning for open-minded discussions of things from making good food to how to find your way in Swedish society. Foreigners living here, Swedes and visitors all welcome to join!

For those who have recently arrived or might have missed it, fika ("fee-ka") is a social institution in Sweden, and in its basic form means having a break with something light to eat and drink. Traditionally it resembles a coffee break, but the beverage can equally well be tea, juice, lemonade or even milk. This is usually accompanied by something sweet, for example a cinnamon roll or cookies. It's an important part of Swedish culture, and a great way to get together and talk about things great and small.

description:
Come join those who like exploring Stockholm on foot, supplied only with sunglasses + smartphone + bottle of water set. 

We define some preliminary route in advance, then on a sunny day step on the road and go! Every meetup is about 2+ hours of walking together in the picturesque surroundings, taking pics, reading out the areas description from wiki or whatever can educate us about the city history and architecture, resting shortly in nearby cafes or places of interest, etc. 

It's all like being a tourist, but why not! Everyday routine somewhat obscures the beauty and the spirit of the city, so let's rediscover it!

P.S. You can also organize walk events yourself! We are democracy and each member can schedule a meetup and invite people for walk!

description:
This Meetup is about having fun and interesting meetings in acknowledgement and recognition of the fact that how we live our days is how we live our lives.

This sounds rather stuffy and formal and boring, but it isn't meant that way. :-)

I am hoping this group will be intellectually curious and wanting to learn and expand its horizon. Let's do meaningful and fun indoor and outdoor activities and try to meet people we will enjoy being around.

Let's pursue such varied interests as hiking and climbing, literature and movies, the martial arts, science and technology, blockchain and economics, entrepreneurship, Paleo/Primal health, eating out, trigger points, parkour, philosophy, and similar stuff - 'stuff' understood here in the highly specific technical sense.

If this sounds like it could be interesting, please join!

By the way, curious about the name? Seneca wrote (hat tip to Brain Pickings https://www.brainpickings.org/2014/09/01/seneca-on-the-shortness-of-life/ for the find):

"It is not that we have a short time to live, but that we waste a lot of it. Life is long enough, and a sufficiently generous amount has been given to us for the highest achievements if it were all well invested. But when it is wasted in heedless luxury and spent on no good activity, we are forced at last by death’s final constraint to realize that it has passed away before we knew it was passing. So it is: we are not given a short life but we make it short, and we are not ill-supplied but wasteful of it… Life is long if you know how to use it."

Group guidelines

- Please cancel any RSVPs if you can't attend - that helps with any bookings, keeping expectations in line, etc.

- Tired of having people upload photos taken of yourself already during the first meet up? Same here - please ask if you'd like to take somebody's photo

- We adhere to the Chatham House Rule: https://www.chathamhouse.org/about/chatham-...

Have fun :-)

description:
Welcome Ladies to Girls In Stockholm!

Girls In Stockholm invites all ladies from all walks of life to join our friendly and lively atmosphere. We are a collection of women from all parts of the world of all ages who come together to share experiences and build lifelong bonds. Once a month, we gather for our monthly fika get together, but throughout the year we also offer a variety of activities which appeal to all types of women.

Event categories:

Outdoor Activities

• Excursions 

• Fitness

• Fun Brunches

 Indoor Activities

• Crafts

• Baking

• Bookclub/Kindle

• Social Fika Intro to Stockholm


Any other suggestions will be welcome. So please do not hesitate to get in touch.


New Girls In Stockholm RSVP rules.

As our organisers and hosts give up their time to arrange these events there will now be a minimum deposit of 50kr when RSVPing. 

When an event is free this money will be refunded upon attendance or a cancellation. Provided the cancellation is in the allotted time.

If these rules are not followed you will immediately be removed from the Girls In Stockholm.
I hope by doing this it will decrease disappointment and let down and encourage friendships and fun.

So with that happy belated New Year from Toyah, Becki Harriet and Shona

category.name: socializing
description:
This is a group for people who enjoy the Swedish (and Scandinavian) tradition of fika. We usually meet Saturday or Sunday morning for open-minded discussions of things from making good food to how to find your way in Swedish society. Foreigners living here, Swedes and visitors all welcome to join!

For those who have recently arrived or might have missed it, fika ("fee-ka") is a social institution in Sweden, and in its basic form means having a break with something light to eat and drink. Traditionally it resembles a coffee break, but the beverage can equally well be tea, juice, lemonade or even milk. This is usually accompanied by something sweet, for example a cinnamon roll or cookies. It's an important part of Swedish culture, and a great way to get together and talk about things great and small.

description:
Come join those who like exploring Stockholm on foot, supplied only with sunglasses + smartphone + bottle of water set. 

We define some preliminary route in advance, then on a sunny day step on the road and go! Every meetup is about 2+ hours of walking together in the picturesque surroundings, taking pics, reading out the areas description from wiki or whatever can educate us about the city history and architecture, resting shortly in nearby cafes or places of interest, etc. 

It's all like being a tourist, but why not! Everyday routine somewhat obscures the beauty and the spirit of the city, so let's rediscover it!

P.S. You can also organize walk events yourself! We are democracy and each member can schedule a meetup and invite people for walk!

description:
This Meetup is about having fun and interesting meetings in acknowledgement and recognition of the fact that how we live our days is how we live our lives.

This sounds rather stuffy and formal and boring, but it isn't meant that way. :-)

I am hoping this group will be intellectually curious and wanting to learn and expand its horizon. Let's do meaningful and fun indoor and outdoor activities and try to meet people we will enjoy being around.

Let's pursue such varied interests as hiking and climbing, literature and movies, the martial arts, science and technology, blockchain and economics, entrepreneurship, Paleo/Primal health, eating out, trigger points, parkour, philosophy, and similar stuff - 'stuff' understood here in the highly specific technical sense.

If this sounds like it could be interesting, please join!

By the way, curious about the name? Seneca wrote (hat tip to Brain Pickings https://www.brainpickings.org/2014/09/01/seneca-on-the-shortness-of-life/ for the find):

"It is not that we have a short time to live, but that we waste a lot of it. Life is long enough, and a sufficiently generous amount has been given to us for the highest achievements if it were all well invested. But when it is wasted in heedless luxury and spent on no good activity, we are forced at last by death’s final constraint to realize that it has passed away before we knew it was passing. So it is: we are not given a short life but we make it short, and we are not ill-supplied but wasteful of it… Life is long if you know how to use it."

Group guidelines

- Please cancel any RSVPs if you can't attend - that helps with any bookings, keeping expectations in line, etc.

- Tired of having people upload photos taken of yourself already during the first meet up? Same here - please ask if you'd like to take somebody's photo

- We adhere to the Chatham House Rule: https://www.chathamhouse.org/about/chatham-...

Have fun :-)

description:
Les Francophones de Copenhague est une association dynamique, non lucrative, dont l'objectif est de permettre aux différents francophones (citoyens de pays francophones, danois francophones et toutes les personnes desirant parler la langue française ) de se rencontrer. Le but de ce groupe est aussi de se faire des amis et de passer d'agréables moments ensemble.

Quelle que soit la raison pour laquelle vous êtes au Danemark (travail, /etudes ou amour), l'arrivée peut être depaysante et solitaire. L'inscription aux Francophones est gratuite et vous êtes libres de choisir les activités auxquelles vous désirez participer. Les organisateurs des Francophones sont bénévoles et organisent les meetups pour le plaisir de rencontrer de nouvelles personnes et de faciliter l'intégration sociale des nouveaux venus.

En devenant membres des Francophones, vous pourrez participer à nos rencontres. La majorité d'entre nous travaillant, les événements ont lieu en soirée ou/et les week-ends. Nos activités incluent rencontres dans des bars, visites de musée, cinéma, conférences (notamment avec l'Institut Français du Danemark) et bien plus. Donc n'hésitez pas à vous inscrire, il y en a pour tous les goûts.

WE ARE HAPPY TO WELCOME DANISH PEOPLE INTO THIS GROUP :-) DON'T BE SHY, JOIN US !!! À bientôt! Vi ses! :-)
name: Les Francophones de Copenhague

category.name: socializing
description:
SOSO BRINGING INTERNATIONALS AND DANES TOGETHER

So Sophisticated started three years ago in a cozy bar with 50 invited friends and acquaintances. It was a mix of internationals and Danes who were encouraged to bring some of their friends along for a comfortable way to socialize while meeting new people and making new friends. Over 100 people ended up coming that very first night and thus, SOSO was born! 

The SOSO initiative was founded on people new to Copenhagen having an opportunity to mix and mingle with Danes for networking and expanding their social circle while getting out and about, being exposed to new places around town for great cocktails. 

For those that may not know a soul and are a bit shy, the people that attend SOSO are welcoming and friendly. You are sure to meet some very nice and interesting people. SOSO is made up of an eclectic bunch of people from ages 25 to 45 who are professionals and students all looking forward to meet you. For those that are outgoing or been with SOSO from the start, it's appreciated that you reach out to the new faces and introduce them to others you know. It's all about getting to know each other. Through SOSO past guests have found new jobs, great friends and even romance.

Come spread the love. We hope to see you and your friends at our next event.

Cheers!
Maria Fazzingo - Founder
Anders Hage - Event Organizer and Host
name: The Copenhagen SOSO Monthly Cocktail Social Club Meetup Grp

description:
By joining the Helsingør - Helsingborg (HH-Meetup) group you will: - participate in common cultural  events and nature excursions in North-west Skaane and Nordsjaelland - get new friends, new opportunities on both sides of oeresund - contribute to H-H and Oeresund as one region - spend a good time in company with good friends - occasionally share events with Meetup groups in Malmö, CPH, Kristianstad and Lund. In some cases you have to count on transport with the boat.

We will: work for integration between a broad number ud cultures and nationalities. Work for understanding and break down frontiers. We arrange a number of events where families can participate as well, the meetup is for everybody!

Please note we are a non-profit meetup and no publicity for private businesses is allowed, excpt for sponsorships of course.

description: Welcome! The expat experience is a life less ordinary. An experience where the value of connections and richness of relations can make the difference between good and great. By connecting spouses who have travelled, lived and worked around the globe we hope to create a fun, inspiring and dynamic group, where we can help each other and share all kinds of experiences and practical advice related to life, travel, family and work in Denmark. As the daughter of an expatriate I grew up in Canada, Egypt and Ivory Coast, and I have spent the last 16 years in Copenhagen. I have worked in the hotel and hospitality business for many years, run my own fashion clothing business and worked in the UN for the last 6 years. Our group is open to all spouses of expatriates and their families as well as Danish expats returning after a few or many years abroad. We are looking forward to hosting a broad array of fun activities and offering you a cosy, warm space to relax and share. Our activities will take place during the day and in the evening, on week days as well as on weekends. Lets make our Copenhagen stay into a fabulous one. See you soon!
name: Copenhagen Expat Spouse meetup

description: Meeting new people can be fun... meeting couples can be twice as much!. Our motto is to build long term friendships, having fun together, learning from and supporting each other. Please know that you must be at least (or soon to be) 30 years old to join us.

category.name: socializing
description:
This group was formed with the aim of expats, and locals for that matter, having the opportunity to meet new people in a comfortable environment. This is a group based on meeting up casually in a bar, park, an outdoor area, or anywhere for that matter. It is about enjoying company, relaxing and having fun over a beer, wine, coffee or any type of drink, anywhere, anytime. 

We are a social group where everyone is welcome, we respect all others in the group (it is not a dating meetup group). 

There is only one expectation in this group: Have fun! If you do not enjoy a meetup, or the venue, then it is best not to come! This group is judgement free. 

Also, please do not hesitate to PM me if you would like to catch up for a coffee or drink at anytime. I hope to see you soon.
name: Copenhagen Casual Meetup Group

category.name: socializing
description:
Our meetup group is organised through the Southern Cross Club. A club for Aussies, Kiwis and their families living in Denmark. Or anyone else with an interest in socialising with Aussies and Kiwis in Denmark.

The club is undoubtedly the oldest club in Denmark. Well before the days of the internet the club was organising a few events each year, and members came from all over Denmark. Today the club is re-establishing itself using social media with the same original intention.

We're looking at different types of events, such as dinners out, pub quizzes, walks in the forest, barbies (of course!), weekends camping, Anzac Day, Christmas parties, etc., etc. All are welcome to use the meetup site to organise or announce their own events.

Find us on Facebook

The Committee - Southern Cross Club, Denmark

description:
Are you a woman loving brunch and looking to make new friends in Copenhagen? If the answer is yes then this is the meetup for you! The objective is to get together on a Saturday/Sunday morning for some brunch/chats and meet new friends. Once a month we'll organize a brunch – from low key to very fancy.

Please be aware that this is a community-driven page that encourages active membership. If you haven't been active in the group for more than 5 month we'll remove you to make room for new members. However, you're always welcome to join us again at a later point. Looking forward to meet you at our next brunch!

This group is limited to 50 members, we therefore have also created a Facebook group where we'll annonce free spots: https://www.facebook.com/groups/587682711569889/

Looking forward to see you at the next brunch!
Martina & Leah

category.name: socializing
description:
Esoteric, for non-native English speakers, is something that is known only by a few people i.e. not mainstream.
As a person who has an avid interest in travel, I would love to go to some places that are quite absurd for many other people. Personally, I engage in travel in a more cultural and leisure way rather than an adventure. That's why I've created this meetup; to find other weirdos like me.
These are places where most of us do not know anybody (although it would be amazing if someone did), where it's hard to convince your friends to travel to, and which are not great for solo travel either.
Some places I have in mind are:
1. The Faroe Islands
2. Riga, Latvia
3. Skopje, Macedonia
4. Tallinn, Estonia
5. Dresden, Germany
Obviously, everyone else can add their own list and we can decide on a place that suits the most number of people. A reasonable target would be to have at least 3 trips in 2018. I would prefer weekend trips, hence the choice of places that are not too far away from CPH and reasonably cheap to fly to. However, this doesn't have to be the case for others. I just want to bring together people with a similar taste, and decide together. About me: 25-year-old Indian guy who moved to CPH last year from the US. I've saved up and ready to take advantage of my Schengen visa with a rather ambitious goal of visiting 12 countries this year.
name: Esoteric European Travel (20's and 30's)

category.name: socializing
description:
Welcome Ladies to Girls In Stockholm!

Girls In Stockholm invites all ladies from all walks of life to join our friendly and lively atmosphere. We are a collection of women from all parts of the world of all ages who come together to share experiences and build lifelong bonds. Once a month, we gather for our monthly fika get together, but throughout the year we also offer a variety of activities which appeal to all types of women.

Event categories:

Outdoor Activities

• Excursions 

• Fitness

• Fun Brunches

 Indoor Activities

• Crafts

• Baking

• Bookclub/Kindle

• Social Fika Intro to Stockholm


Any other suggestions will be welcome. So please do not hesitate to get in touch.


New Girls In Stockholm RSVP rules.

As our organisers and hosts give up their time to arrange these events there will now be a minimum deposit of 50kr when RSVPing. 

When an event is free this money will be refunded upon attendance or a cancellation. Provided the cancellation is in the allotted time.

If these rules are not followed you will immediately be removed from the Girls In Stockholm.
I hope by doing this it will decrease disappointment and let down and encourage friendships and fun.

So with that happy belated New Year from Toyah, Becki Harriet and Shona

description:
This is a group for people who enjoy the Swedish (and Scandinavian) tradition of fika. We usually meet Saturday or Sunday morning for open-minded discussions of things from making good food to how to find your way in Swedish society. Foreigners living here, Swedes and visitors all welcome to join!

For those who have recently arrived or might have missed it, fika ("fee-ka") is a social institution in Sweden, and in its basic form means having a break with something light to eat and drink. Traditionally it resembles a coffee break, but the beverage can equally well be tea, juice, lemonade or even milk. This is usually accompanied by something sweet, for example a cinnamon roll or cookies. It's an important part of Swedish culture, and a great way to get together and talk about things great and small.

description:
Come join those who like exploring Stockholm on foot, supplied only with sunglasses + smartphone + bottle of water set. 

We define some preliminary route in advance, then on a sunny day step on the road and go! Every meetup is about 2+ hours of walking together in the picturesque surroundings, taking pics, reading out the areas description from wiki or whatever can educate us about the city history and architecture, resting shortly in nearby cafes or places of interest, etc. 

It's all like being a tourist, but why not! Everyday routine somewhat obscures the beauty and the spirit of the city, so let's rediscover it!

P.S. You can also organize walk events yourself! We are democracy and each member can schedule a meetup and invite people for walk!

category.name: socializing
description:
This Meetup is about having fun and interesting meetings in acknowledgement and recognition of the fact that how we live our days is how we live our lives.

This sounds rather stuffy and formal and boring, but it isn't meant that way. :-)

I am hoping this group will be intellectually curious and wanting to learn and expand its horizon. Let's do meaningful and fun indoor and outdoor activities and try to meet people we will enjoy being around.

Let's pursue such varied interests as hiking and climbing, literature and movies, the martial arts, science and technology, blockchain and economics, entrepreneurship, Paleo/Primal health, eating out, trigger points, parkour, philosophy, and similar stuff - 'stuff' understood here in the highly specific technical sense.

If this sounds like it could be interesting, please join!

By the way, curious about the name? Seneca wrote (hat tip to Brain Pickings https://www.brainpickings.org/2014/09/01/seneca-on-the-shortness-of-life/ for the find):

"It is not that we have a short time to live, but that we waste a lot of it. Life is long enough, and a sufficiently generous amount has been given to us for the highest achievements if it were all well invested. But when it is wasted in heedless luxury and spent on no good activity, we are forced at last by death’s final constraint to realize that it has passed away before we knew it was passing. So it is: we are not given a short life but we make it short, and we are not ill-supplied but wasteful of it… Life is long if you know how to use it."

Group guidelines

- Please cancel any RSVPs if you can't attend - that helps with any bookings, keeping expectations in line, etc.

- Tired of having people upload photos taken of yourself already during the first meet up? Same here - please ask if you'd like to take somebody's photo

- We adhere to the Chatham House Rule: https://www.chathamhouse.org/about/chatham-...

Have fun :-)
name: Living like Seneca

description:
Les Francophones de Copenhague est une association dynamique, non lucrative, dont l'objectif est de permettre aux différents francophones (citoyens de pays francophones, danois francophones et toutes les personnes desirant parler la langue française ) de se rencontrer. Le but de ce groupe est aussi de se faire des amis et de passer d'agréables moments ensemble.

Quelle que soit la raison pour laquelle vous êtes au Danemark (travail, /etudes ou amour), l'arrivée peut être depaysante et solitaire. L'inscription aux Francophones est gratuite et vous êtes libres de choisir les activités auxquelles vous désirez participer. Les organisateurs des Francophones sont bénévoles et organisent les meetups pour le plaisir de rencontrer de nouvelles personnes et de faciliter l'intégration sociale des nouveaux venus.

En devenant membres des Francophones, vous pourrez participer à nos rencontres. La majorité d'entre nous travaillant, les événements ont lieu en soirée ou/et les week-ends. Nos activités incluent rencontres dans des bars, visites de musée, cinéma, conférences (notamment avec l'Institut Français du Danemark) et bien plus. Donc n'hésitez pas à vous inscrire, il y en a pour tous les goûts.

WE ARE HAPPY TO WELCOME DANISH PEOPLE INTO THIS GROUP :-) DON'T BE SHY, JOIN US !!! À bientôt! Vi ses! :-)
name: Les Francophones de Copenhague

category.name: socializing
description:
SOSO BRINGING INTERNATIONALS AND DANES TOGETHER

So Sophisticated started three years ago in a cozy bar with 50 invited friends and acquaintances. It was a mix of internationals and Danes who were encouraged to bring some of their friends along for a comfortable way to socialize while meeting new people and making new friends. Over 100 people ended up coming that very first night and thus, SOSO was born! 

The SOSO initiative was founded on people new to Copenhagen having an opportunity to mix and mingle with Danes for networking and expanding their social circle while getting out and about, being exposed to new places around town for great cocktails. 

For those that may not know a soul and are a bit shy, the people that attend SOSO are welcoming and friendly. You are sure to meet some very nice and interesting people. SOSO is made up of an eclectic bunch of people from ages 25 to 45 who are professionals and students all looking forward to meet you. For those that are outgoing or been with SOSO from the start, it's appreciated that you reach out to the new faces and introduce them to others you know. It's all about getting to know each other. Through SOSO past guests have found new jobs, great friends and even romance.

Come spread the love. We hope to see you and your friends at our next event.

Cheers!
Maria Fazzingo - Founder
Anders Hage - Event Organizer and Host

description: Welcome! The expat experience is a life less ordinary. An experience where the value of connections and richness of relations can make the difference between good and great. By connecting spouses who have travelled, lived and worked around the globe we hope to create a fun, inspiring and dynamic group, where we can help each other and share all kinds of experiences and practical advice related to life, travel, family and work in Denmark. As the daughter of an expatriate I grew up in Canada, Egypt and Ivory Coast, and I have spent the last 16 years in Copenhagen. I have worked in the hotel and hospitality business for many years, run my own fashion clothing business and worked in the UN for the last 6 years. Our group is open to all spouses of expatriates and their families as well as Danish expats returning after a few or many years abroad. We are looking forward to hosting a broad array of fun activities and offering you a cosy, warm space to relax and share. Our activities will take place during the day and in the evening, on week days as well as on weekends. Lets make our Copenhagen stay into a fabulous one. See you soon!
name: Copenhagen Expat Spouse meetup

Hi new friend, are you looking for making friends easily ... in small friendly groups?


Are you tired with too noisy, too big or too trendy events with hundreds of people that you never talk? Maybe a friendly event is just about :

• a small group of 6 or 8 people

• having enough time to talk and know each other

Send me a friendly message if you like this idea...

Cheers, Anna

description: Meeting new people can be fun... meeting couples can be twice as much!. This is a group intended for couples only, so we'll consider everyone who joins as an RSVP+1, which means you are in a relationship, have a wifey or a hubby, a partner, a boo or a bae, a special someone, a significant other, however you wanna call it, the thing is you're not alone and will always attend in pairs. Our events will be tailored for couples: dinner parties, BBQs, boat trips, picnics, sightseeing, bike rides, movies, game nights, etc., and all RSVPs will be counted as two people, even when not adding the plus one. Our motto is to build long term friendships, having fun together, learning from and supporting each other. Please know that you must be at least (or soon to be) 30 years old to join us.

Together, we want to create value in the community. 

Café Cadeau - coffee, people and culture.

description:
This group was formed with the aim of expats, and locals for that matter, having the opportunity to meet new people in a comfortable environment. This is a group based on meeting up casually in a bar, park, an outdoor area, or anywhere for that matter. It is about enjoying company, relaxing and having fun over a beer, wine, coffee or any type of drink, anywhere, anytime. 

We are a social group where everyone is welcome, we respect all others in the group (it is not a dating meetup group). 

There is only one expectation in this group: Have fun! If you do not enjoy a meetup, or the venue, then it is best not to come! This group is judgement free. 

Also, please do not hesitate to PM me if you would like to catch up for a coffee or drink at anytime. I hope to see you soon.

description:
Our meetup group is organised through the Southern Cross Club. A club for Aussies, Kiwis and their families living in Denmark. Or anyone else with an interest in socialising with Aussies and Kiwis in Denmark.

The club is undoubtedly the oldest club in Denmark. Well before the days of the internet the club was organising a few events each year, and members came from all over Denmark. Today the club is re-establishing itself using social media with the same original intention.

We're looking at different types of events, such as dinners out, pub quizzes, walks in the forest, barbies (of course!), weekends camping, Anzac Day, Christmas parties, etc., etc. All are welcome to use the meetup site to organise or announce their own events.

Find us on Facebook

The Committee - Southern Cross Club, Denmark

category.name: socializing
description:
Esoteric, for non-native English speakers, is something that is known only by a few people i.e. not mainstream.
As a person who has an avid interest in travel, I would love to go to some places that are quite absurd for many other people. Personally, I engage in travel in a more cultural and leisure way rather than an adventure. That's why I've created this meetup; to find other weirdos like me.
These are places where most of us do not know anybody (although it would be amazing if someone did), where it's hard to convince your friends to travel to, and which are not great for solo travel either.
Some places I have in mind are:
1. The Faroe Islands
2. Riga, Latvia
3. Skopje, Macedonia
4. Tallinn, Estonia
5. Dresden, Germany
Obviously, everyone else can add their own list and we can decide on a place that suits the most number of people. A reasonable target would be to have at least 3 trips in 2018. I would prefer weekend trips, hence the choice of places that are not too far away from CPH and reasonably cheap to fly to. However, this doesn't have to be the case for others. I just want to bring together people with a similar taste, and decide together. About me: 25-year-old Indian guy who moved to CPH last year from the US. I've saved up and ready to take advantage of my Schengen visa with a rather ambitious goal of visiting 12 countries this year.
name: Esoteric European Travel (20's and 30's)

description:
We are a group of women who get together to socialize, celebrate and enjoy being American. Yes that includes celebrating the 4th of July, Thanksgiving, and more! AWCG is primarily a support group for fellow American expats, but it is also great way to meet new people, have access to a great network of women, and find a piece of home away from home. If you have a question, we've probably asked it. We are a wealth of information and always willing to share our experiences.

Not an American expat? We also welcome non-citizen ladies with strong connections to the U.S. such as having an American sambo or children, or those who have worked, lived, or studied in the U.S. for a long period of time.

Learn more about us on our website.

Unsure if this club is for you? Please send an inquiry to membership(at)awcgothenburg.com before filling out a membership form.

category.name: socializing
description:
Welcome Ladies to Girls In Stockholm!

Girls In Stockholm invites all ladies from all walks of life to join our friendly and lively atmosphere. We are a collection of women from all parts of the world of all ages who come together to share experiences and build lifelong bonds. Once a month, we gather for our monthly fika get together, but throughout the year we also offer a variety of activities which appeal to all types of women.

Event categories:

Outdoor Activities

• Excursions 

• Fitness

• Fun Brunches

 Indoor Activities

• Crafts

• Baking

• Bookclub/Kindle

• Social Fika Intro to Stockholm


Any other suggestions will be welcome. So please do not hesitate to get in touch.


New Girls In Stockholm RSVP rules.

As our organisers and hosts give up their time to arrange these events there will now be a minimum deposit of 50kr when RSVPing. 

When an event is free this money will be refunded upon attendance or a cancellation. Provided the cancellation is in the allotted time.

If these rules are not followed you will immediately be removed from the Girls In Stockholm.
I hope by doing this it will decrease disappointment and let down and encourage friendships and fun.

So with that happy belated New Year from Toyah, Becki Harriet and Shona

description:
This is a group for people who enjoy the Swedish (and Scandinavian) tradition of fika. We usually meet Saturday or Sunday morning for open-minded discussions of things from making good food to how to find your way in Swedish society. Foreigners living here, Swedes and visitors all welcome to join!

For those who have recently arrived or might have missed it, fika ("fee-ka") is a social institution in Sweden, and in its basic form means having a break with something light to eat and drink. Traditionally it resembles a coffee break, but the beverage can equally well be tea, juice, lemonade or even milk. This is usually accompanied by something sweet, for example a cinnamon roll or cookies. It's an important part of Swedish culture, and a great way to get together and talk about things great and small.

description:
Come join those who like exploring Stockholm on foot, supplied only with sunglasses + smartphone + bottle of water set. 

We define some preliminary route in advance, then on a sunny day step on the road and go! Every meetup is about 2+ hours of walking together in the picturesque surroundings, taking pics, reading out the areas description from wiki or whatever can educate us about the city history and architecture, resting shortly in nearby cafes or places of interest, etc. 

It's all like being a tourist, but why not! Everyday routine somewhat obscures the beauty and the spirit of the city, so let's rediscover it!

P.S. You can also organize walk events yourself! We are democracy and each member can schedule a meetup and invite people for walk!

category.name: socializing
description:
This Meetup is about having fun and interesting meetings in acknowledgement and recognition of the fact that how we live our days is how we live our lives.

This sounds rather stuffy and formal and boring, but it isn't meant that way. :-)

I am hoping this group will be intellectually curious and wanting to learn and expand its horizon. Let's do meaningful and fun indoor and outdoor activities and try to meet people we will enjoy being around.

Let's pursue such varied interests as hiking and climbing, literature and movies, the martial arts, science and technology, blockchain and economics, entrepreneurship, Paleo/Primal health, eating out, trigger points, parkour, philosophy, and similar stuff - 'stuff' understood here in the highly specific technical sense.

If this sounds like it could be interesting, please join!

By the way, curious about the name? Seneca wrote (hat tip to Brain Pickings https://www.brainpickings.org/2014/09/01/seneca-on-the-shortness-of-life/ for the find):

"It is not that we have a short time to live, but that we waste a lot of it. Life is long enough, and a sufficiently generous amount has been given to us for the highest achievements if it were all well invested. But when it is wasted in heedless luxury and spent on no good activity, we are forced at last by death’s final constraint to realize that it has passed away before we knew it was passing. So it is: we are not given a short life but we make it short, and we are not ill-supplied but wasteful of it… Life is long if you know how to use it."

Group guidelines

- Please cancel any RSVPs if you can't attend - that helps with any bookings, keeping expectations in line, etc.

- Tired of having people upload photos taken of yourself already during the first meet up? Same here - please ask if you'd like to take somebody's photo

- We adhere to the Chatham House Rule: https://www.chathamhouse.org/about/chatham-...

Have fun :-)
name: Living like Seneca

category.name: socializing
description:
Welcome Ladies to Girls In Stockholm!

Girls In Stockholm invites all ladies from all walks of life to join our friendly and lively atmosphere. We are a collection of women from all parts of the world of all ages who come together to share experiences and build lifelong bonds. Once a month, we gather for our monthly fika get together, but throughout the year we also offer a variety of activities which appeal to all types of women.

Event categories:

Outdoor Activities

• Excursions 

• Fitness

• Fun Brunches

 Indoor Activities

• Crafts

• Baking

• Bookclub/Kindle

• Social Fika Intro to Stockholm


Any other suggestions will be welcome. So please do not hesitate to get in touch.


New Girls In Stockholm RSVP rules.

As our organisers and hosts give up their time to arrange these events there will now be a minimum deposit of 50kr when RSVPing. 

When an event is free this money will be refunded upon attendance or a cancellation. Provided the cancellation is in the allotted time.

If these rules are not followed you will immediately be removed from the Girls In Stockholm.
I hope by doing this it will decrease disappointment and let down and encourage friendships and fun.

So with that happy belated New Year from Toyah, Becki Harriet and Shona

category.name: socializing
description:
This is a group for people who enjoy the Swedish (and Scandinavian) tradition of fika. We usually meet Saturday or Sunday morning for open-minded discussions of things from making good food to how to find your way in Swedish society. Foreigners living here, Swedes and visitors all welcome to join!

For those who have recently arrived or might have missed it, fika ("fee-ka") is a social institution in Sweden, and in its basic form means having a break with something light to eat and drink. Traditionally it resembles a coffee break, but the beverage can equally well be tea, juice, lemonade or even milk. This is usually accompanied by something sweet, for example a cinnamon roll or cookies. It's an important part of Swedish culture, and a great way to get together and talk about things great and small.

description:
Come join those who like exploring Stockholm on foot, supplied only with sunglasses + smartphone + bottle of water set. 

We define some preliminary route in advance, then on a sunny day step on the road and go! Every meetup is about 2+ hours of walking together in the picturesque surroundings, taking pics, reading out the areas description from wiki or whatever can educate us about the city history and architecture, resting shortly in nearby cafes or places of interest, etc. 

It's all like being a tourist, but why not! Everyday routine somewhat obscures the beauty and the spirit of the city, so let's rediscover it!

P.S. You can also organize walk events yourself! We are democracy and each member can schedule a meetup and invite people for walk!
